"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of the enactment of the William M. (Mac) Thornberry National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2021, referred to in subsec. (b)(1), is the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The National Environmental Policy Act of 1969, referred to in subsec. (b)(5), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/190"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–190","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/852"},"text":"83 Stat. 852","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 55 (§ 4321 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s4321"},"text":"section 4321 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The date of the enactment of the James M. Inhofe National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2023, referred to in subsec. (h)(1), is the date of enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2022","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab55beba-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (b)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s10303/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 10303(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s10303/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 10303(a)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (c) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “In discharging its responsibilities in support of agreed-upon scientific needs, and to assist in the execution of the responsibilities described in subsection (b), the Committee may delegate responsibilities to a subcommittee of the Committee, as the Committee determines appropriate.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (h), (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s10303/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 10303(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (h) and redesignated former subsec. (h) as (i)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1055/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1055(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Ocean Policy Committee” for “National Ocean Research Leadership Council” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (a) to (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1055/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1055(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (B), added subsecs. (a) to (e) and struck out former subsecs. (a) to (e) which related to establishment, membership, chairman and vice chairman, responsibilities, and annual reports of the National Ocean Research Leadership Council."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1055/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1055(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (C), (D), redesignated subsec. (g) as (f), substituted “Committee” for “Council” wherever appearing, and struck out former subsec. (f) which related to establishment of a partnership program office for the National Oceanographic Partnership Program."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1055/b/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1055(b)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", (D), redesignated subsec. (h) as (g) and substituted “Committee” for “Council”. Former subsec. (g) redesignated (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1055/b/1/E"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1055(b)(1)(E)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (h). Former subsec. (h) redesignated (g)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s7902"},"text":"section 7902 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (b)(13), (14). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296","children":[],"tail":" added pars. (13) and (14)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsec. (e)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/65"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–65","children":[],"tail":" struck out “, United States Code,” after “title 31”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (b)(8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/s1073/a/64"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, § 1073(a)(64)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “United States” before “Geological Survey”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(11) to (13). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/s241/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, § 241(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated pars. (12) and (13) as (11) and (12), respectively, and struck out former par. (11) which read as follows: “The President of the National Academy of Sciences, the President of the National Academy of Engineering, and the President of the Institute of Medicine.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(14) to (17). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/s241/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, § 241(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", struck out pars. (14) to (17) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(14) One member appointed by the chairman from among individuals who will represent the views of ocean industries.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(15) One member appointed by the chairman from among individuals who will represent the views of State governments.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(16) One member appointed by the chairman from among individuals who will represent the views of academia.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(17) One member appointed by the chairman from among individuals who will represent such other views as the chairman considers appropriate.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (d) to (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/s241/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, § 241(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated subsecs. (e) to (i) as (d) to (h), respectively, and struck out former subsec. (d) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(d) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Term of Office","children":[],"tail":".—The term of office of a member of the Council appointed under paragraph (14), (15), (16), or (17) of subsection (b) shall be two years, except that any person appointed to fill a vacancy occurring before the expiration of the term for which his predecessor was appointed shall be appointed for the remainder of such term.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":